-- Nedbank Unit Aims for Double-Digit Growth, Business Day Says
-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 2012-03-30T05:16:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/nedbank-unit-aims-for-double-digit-growth-business-day-says.html
Nedbank Capital, the investment
banking unit of  Nedbank Group Ltd. (NED) , plans to grow earnings
excluding one-time items in the “double digits” this year as
it funds infrastructure and renewable energy projects, Business
Day reported, citing Managing Executive  Brian Kennedy .  The bank plans to provide funding in the second phase of
South Africa’s renewable energy independent power producer
program, the Johannesburg-based newspaper cited Kennedy as
saying. Opportunities also existed to finance mergers and
acquisitions between junior miners, it quoted Terence Sibiya,
executive head of coverage and origination at the bank as
saying.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Gunnion at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net  